&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;GP Maternity Locum 5 - 6 sessions&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a GP Locum for a period of 8-9 months from Mid-January 2021 to cover maternity leave.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Chipping Norton Health Centre is situated in a brand new purpose built building on the edge of the Cotswolds and is a modern, innovative practice. We provide primary health care to the residents of Chipping Norton and the surrounding rural area, local nursing and residential homes and the community hospital.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are a training practice with 5 partners, 7 salaried GPs, ST3s, FY2s and medical students. Our multidisciplinary team includes nurse practitioners, paramedics, physiotherapist and a clinical pharmacist. Our highly regarded and skilled primary care team looks after 15,800 patients and achieves high QoF each year. We use EMIS web, docman, accuRx and Lexacom. In house specialties include minor surgery, dermoscopy, LARC fitting, joint injections and acupuncture.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Benefits we offer: - your indemnity included, 7 weeks annual/study leave (pro rata), blocked admin time, monthly educational meetings.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applications are invited from interested GPs (or current registrars) to cover up to 5/6 sessions per week. There is also the opportunity to cover extended hours and local hub appointments.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Informal visits are always welcome.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
